habitat_description:
Stebbins 2003, has P.maculata included in the range of P. triseriata. But, 
Conant and Collins 1998 have P. triseriata triseriata. Ranges from extreme south Quebec and adjacent New York, to Kansas and Oklahoma. Moreover, this species is found in Michigan, southern Ontario, Indiana, western Kentucky, northwestern Tennessee, and southern Illinois (Lemmon et al. 2007). Dodd (2013) and Green et al. (2013) have the species as described above.  

Behler and King (1979) describe the preferred habitat for the species as grassy areas including swampy, dry, and even agricultural areas. Furthermore, this species also expand from river swamps and woodlands into suburban areas with low pesticide problems.
